    "<?xml version=\"1.0\"?><rss version=\"2.0\"><channel><title>House Floor Proceedings</title><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx</link><description>House Floor proceedings of the previous 1 legislative days, including current legislative days in progress.</description><language>en-US</language><pubDate>Sat, 24 Jun 2017 19:01:14 GMT</pubDate><lastBuildDate>Sat, 24 Jun 2017 19:01:14 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 12:51:58 P.M.</title><description>\nThe House adjourned pursuant to a previous special order. The next meeting is scheduled for 12:00 p.m. on June 26, 2017.\n</description><guid>20170623T12:51:58</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 16:53:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 12:51:57 P.M.</title><description>\nOn motion to adjourn Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T12:51:57</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 16:53:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 12:51:50 P.M.</title><description>\nMr. Gohmert moved that the House do now adjourn.\n</description><guid>20170623T12:51:50</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 16:53:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 12:51:27 P.M.</title><description>\nThe House received a communication from Representative Chaffetz wherein he resigns as a member of the House of Representatives effective at 10:00 a.m. on June 30, 2017.\n</description><guid>20170623T12:51:27</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 16:53:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 11:23:48 A.M.</title><description>\nSPECIAL ORDER SPEECHES - The House has concluded all anticipated legislative business and has proceeded to Special Order speeches.\n</description><guid>20170623T11:23:48</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:23:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 11:03:16 A.M.</title><description>\nONE MINUTE SPEECHES - The House proceeded with further one minute speeches.\n</description><guid>20170623T11:03:16</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:04:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 11:02:55 A.M.</title><description>\nMr. Curbelo (FL) asked unanimous consent That when the House adjourns on Friday, June 23, 2017, it adjourn to meet on Monday, June 26, 2017, when it shall convene at noon for Morning-Hour debate and 2 p.m. for legislative buisness. Agreed to without objection.\n</description><guid>20170623T11:02:55</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:14:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 11:02:28 A.M.</title><description>\nMotion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.\n</description><guid>20170623T11:02:28</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:02:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 11:02:26 A.M.</title><description>\nOn passage Passed by the Yeas and Nays: 377 - 34 &lt;a rel=\"vote\" href=\"http://clerk.house.gov/cgi-bin/vote.asp?year=2017&amp;amp;rollnumber=322\"&gt;(Roll no. 322)&lt;/a&gt;.\n</description><guid>20170623T11:02:26</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:17:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:55:19 A.M.</title><description>\nThe House adopted the amendment in the nature of a substitute as agreed to by the Committee of the Whole House on the state of the Union.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:55:19</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:56:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:55:10 A.M.</title><description>\nThe previous question was ordered pursuant to the rule.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:55:10</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:56:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:54:34 A.M.</title><description>\nThe House rose from the Committee of the Whole House on the state of the Union to report &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;H.R. 2842&lt;/a&gt;.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:54:34</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:56:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:54:15 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Davidson amendment; Agreed to by recorded vote: 264 - 147 &lt;a rel=\"vote\" href=\"http://clerk.house.gov/cgi-bin/vote.asp?year=2017&amp;amp;rollnumber=321\"&gt;(Roll no. 321)&lt;/a&gt;.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:54:15</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:17:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:48:02 A.M.</title><description>\nThe House resolved into Committee of the Whole House on the state of the Union for further consideration.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:48:02</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:56:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:47:07 A.M.</title><description>\nConsidered as unfinished business. &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;H.R. 2842&lt;/a&gt; — \"&lt;b&gt;To provide for the conduct of demonstration projects to test the effectiveness of subsidized employment for TANF recipients&lt;/b&gt;.\"\n</description><guid>20170623T10:47:07</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:56:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:43:52 A.M.</title><description>\nHOUSE DECORUM - The Speaker assumed the Chair and addressed the Members on matters of decorum in the House. At the conclusion of his remarks, the Speaker announced that the Committee of the Whole resume with voting on H.R. 2842.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:43:52</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:01:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:43:45 A.M.</title><description>\nCommittee of the Whole House on the state of the Union rises leaving &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;H.R. 2842&lt;/a&gt; as unfinished business.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:43:45</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:44:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:43:36 A.M.</title><description>\nOn motion that the committee rise Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:43:36</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:44:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:43:22 A.M.</title><description>\nMr. Smith (NE) moved that the committee rise.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:43:22</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:44:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:43:09 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Krishnamoorthi amendment; Agreed to by recorded vote: 380 - 32 &lt;a rel=\"vote\" href=\"http://clerk.house.gov/cgi-bin/vote.asp?year=2017&amp;amp;rollnumber=320\"&gt;(Roll no. 320)&lt;/a&gt;.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:43:09</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 15:17:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:12:19 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Kilmer amendment; Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:12:19</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:13:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:08:47 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Kilmer amendment No. 7.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:08:47</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:11:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:08:28 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Mr. Kilmer,  numbered 7 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to require the Secretary to address employment-related challenges in rural areas and among members of federally recognized Indian tribes in the recommendations provided to Congress.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:08:28</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:11:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:08:19 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Khanna amendment; Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:08:19</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:09:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:04:55 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Khanna amendment No. 6.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:04:55</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:06:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:04:37 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Mr. Khanna,  numbered 6 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to direct HHS to measure the effect of training and credentialing in its evaluation to the public and recommendations to Congress.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:04:37</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:06:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 10:04:14 A.M.</title><description>\nPOSTPONED PROCEEDINGS - At the conclusion of debate on the Davidson amendment No. 5, the Chair put the question on adoption of the amendment and by voice vote, announced that the ayes had prevailed. Mr. Davis (IL) demanded a recorded vote and the Chair postponed further proceedings until later in the legislative day.\n</description><guid>20170623T10:04:14</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:07:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:58:05 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Davidson amendment No. 5.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:58:05</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:59:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:57:44 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Mr. Davidson,  numbered 5 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to direct states to include in their end of the fiscal year report the number of recipients who received additional federal or state means-tested benefits during their subsidized employment.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:57:44</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:48:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:57:05 A.M.</title><description>\nPOSTPONED PROCEEDINGS - At the conclusion of debate on the Krishnamoorthi amendment No. 4, the Chair put the question on adoption of the amendment and by voice vote, announced that the ayes had prevailed. Mr. Smith (NE) demanded a recorded vote and the Chair postponed further proceedings until later in the legislative day.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:57:05</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:03:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:54:31 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Krishnamoorthi amendment No. 4.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:54:31</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:56:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:54:14 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Mr. Krishnamoorthi,  numbered 4 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to require states to report on the number of individuals who are in a career that matches their training.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:54:14</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 14:12:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:53:59 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Bonamici amendment; Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:53:59</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:54:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:48:23 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Bonamici amendment No. 3.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:48:23</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:50:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:48:05 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Ms. Bonamici,  numbered 3 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to require states to coordinate the subsidized employment program authorized in the bill with other federal workforce development programs, including the Federal Work Study Program.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:48:05</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:50:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:47:55 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Bost amendment; Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:47:55</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:48:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:44:31 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Bost amendment No. 2.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:44:31</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:46:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:44:13 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Mr. Bost,  numbered 2 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to ensure that states include in their applications how they will use the funds to help individuals who have been displaced or relocated from a public housing authority to an alternative public housing facility or placed on rental assistance.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:44:13</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:46:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:44:04 A.M.</title><description>\nOn agreeing to the Foxx amendment; Agreed to by voice vote.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:44:04</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:44:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:40:58 A.M.</title><description>\nDEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Foxx amendment No. 1.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:40:58</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:43:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:40:40 A.M.</title><description>\nAn amendment, offered by Ms. Foxx,  numbered 1 printed in &lt;a rel=\"report\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/115th-congress/house-report/187\"&gt;House Report 115-187&lt;/a&gt; to encourage better coordination with state workforce development efforts and adds to the reporting requirements in Section 5 to describe efforts by the State to ensure nondisplacement and establish grievance procedures.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:40:40</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:43:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:11:13 A.M.</title><description>\nGENERAL DEBATE - The Committee of the Whole proceeded with one hour of general debate on &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;&lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;H.R. 2842&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:11:13</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:12:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:11:02 A.M.</title><description>\nThe Speaker designated the Honorable Jeff Denham to act as Chairman of the Committee.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:11:02</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:12:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:11:01 A.M.</title><description>\nHouse resolved itself into the Committee of the Whole House on the state of the Union pursuant to &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt; and Rule XVIII.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:11:01</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:12:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:10:33 A.M.</title><description>\nRule provides for consideration of &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;H.R. 2842&lt;/a&gt; with 1 hour of general debate. Motion to recommit with or without instructions allowed. The resolution makes in order as original text for the purpose of amendment an amendment in the nature of a substitute consisting of the text of Rules Committee Print 115-22. The resolution makes in order only those further amendments printed in the Rules Committee report. Also, the resolution makes in order at any time on the legislative day of June 22, 2017, for the Speaker to entertain motion that the House suspend the rules relating to the bill &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2353\"&gt;H.R. 2353&lt;/a&gt;.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:10:33</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:11:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:10:28 A.M.</title><description>\nConsidered under the provisions of rule &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-resolution/396\"&gt;H. Res. 396&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a rel=\"bill\" href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2842\"&gt;H.R. 2842&lt;/a&gt; — \"&lt;b&gt;To provide for the conduct of demonstration projects to test the effectiveness of subsidized employment for TANF recipients&lt;/b&gt;.\"\n</description><guid>20170623T09:10:28</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:11:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:01:44 A.M.</title><description>\nONE MINUTE SPEECHES - The House proceeded with one minute speeches which by direction of the Chair, would be limited to 5 per side of the aisle.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:01:44</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:02:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:01:28 A.M.</title><description>\nPLEDGE OF ALLEGIANCE - The Chair designated Mr. Heck to lead the Members in reciting the Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:01:28</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:01:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:01:26 A.M.</title><description>\nThe Speaker announced approval of the Journal.  Pursuant to clause 1, rule I, the Journal stands approved.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:01:26</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:01:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:00:27 A.M.</title><description>\nToday's prayer was offered by the House Chaplain, Rev. Patrick J. Conroy.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:00:27</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:00:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item><item><title>Legislative Day Of June 23, 2017  - 9:00:22 A.M.</title><description>\nThe House convened, starting a new legislative day.\n</description><guid>20170623T09:00:22</guid><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 13:00:00 GMT</pubDate><link>http://clerk.house.gov/floorsummary/floor.aspx?day=20170623</link></item></channel></rss>"
    |> SweetXml.parse
    |> SweetXml.xmap(mapping)
  end

